## Working Rules

- Keep the public surface small and documented.
- Prefer one boring command per task: install, lint, typecheck, test, build, docs, publish.
- Update `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/`, and `llms.txt` when behavior changes.
- Do not add stack details to the README unless users need them to install or run the project.
- Do not commit, tag, publish, or push unless explicitly asked.

## Commands

The dev environment is managed by [chefe](https://phvv.me/chefe), which compiles `chefe.toml` and runs the real tools.

- Install: `chefe install`
- Lint: `chefe run lint`
- Typecheck: `chefe run typecheck`
- Test: `chefe run test`
- Docs: `chefe run docs`
- Build: `uv build`

